s in a follow-up PR on `unh_marine_autonomy`, or (b) re-run the improved skill to regenerate everything. |\n| Only what's needed | OK | Three targeted fixes, no over-engineering. |\n| Capture decisions, not just implementations | Watch | The root cause analysis is excellent — it documents *why* errors occurred, not just what to change. Worth preserving in a commit message or the SKILL.md itself so future maintainers understand the design choices. |\n\n### ADR Applicability\n\n| ADR | Triggered | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| 0003 — Project-agnostic workspace | Yes | The skill is generic workspace infra, not project-specific. The fixes keep it that way. OK. |\n| 0006 — Shared AGENTS.md | No | Skill changes don't affect AGENTS.md or adapters. |\n\n### Consequences\n\nFrom the consequences map:\n\n| If you change... | Also update... | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| A framework skill (`.claude/skills/`) | Framework adapter file; regenerate skills if needed | Needed — check if `CLAUDE.md` or skill list references need updating (likely not for a bugfix, but verify) |\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Explicitly scope the data fix: should this issue also cover a follow-up PR on `unh_marine_autonomy` to correct the 34 profiles, or is that a separate issue?\n- Consider whether proposed fix #1 (structured intermediate format) could be a simple helper script (e.g., `find */package.xml -exec xmllint --xpath '//name/text()' {} \\;`) rather than relying on agent discipline. This would align with \"enforcement over documentation.\"\n- The issue mentions \"3 of 34 profiles\" were spot-checked. A full audit of all 34 profiles would be valuable to understand the true error rate and whether fixes need to be broader than the 3 proposed changes suggest.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772233993,"nonce":"bRECZPG25/P7M/uxoQlq8qFau8U=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87um_z-zwAAAAVjz6Y5"},"status":2}]}